# Bellum Gero – AI Context

User may state at session start: **"We're on Shadow PC"** or **"We're on the WSL dev server."** Follow the matching context below.
However, you can tell by the directory path for Shadow PC 'C:\Users\Shadow' **"We're on Shadow PC"** else **"We're on the WSL dev server."**

## CURRENT CONTEXT

- **Shadow PC (this dev box):** Windows only. No WSL. Coding and asset editing only. Repo path e.g. `C:\Users\Shadow\code\swg-bg`. Do NOT suggest build/run/test here. Use Windows paths. Git/SSH from PowerShell or Git Bash. Optional TRE/map editing; game uses TREs on WSL server.
- **WSL dev server:** Linux (WSL Debian). Build, run, test Core3. Project root `~/localswgserver`. TREs at `/trefiles`. Database, config, run instructions apply here.

## PROJECT

SWGEmu-based Pre-CU server **SWG Bellum Gero** – tailored gameplay, custom content, lore-appropriate design.

## CORE BEHAVIOR

- **Project location:** WSL = `~/localswgserver`. Shadow PC = cloned repo (e.g. `C:\Users\Shadow\code\swg-bg`), Windows paths.
- **LUA FIRST:** Add items/NPCs/stats/spawns/loot/conversations/quests via `MMOCoreORB/bin/scripts/` first. C++ only if impossible in Lua. Shadow: `<clone>\MMOCoreORB\bin\scripts\`. WSL: `~/localswgserver/MMOCoreORB/bin/scripts/`.
- **Database/config (WSL only):** `~/localswgserver/MMOCoreORB/bin/conf/config.lua` and `config-local.lua`.
- **Local dev guide (WSL only):** `~/localswgserver/LOCAL_DEV_ENV_SETUP.md`.
- **WSL workflow (WSL only):** Commands in WSL Debian; build in WSL. On Shadow PC: no WSL; Git only from PowerShell/Git Bash.
- **Build blockers (WSL only):** DPP (pkg-config dpp), GCC -Werror, engine3 submodule in CHANGELOG.
- **Troubleshooting (WSL only):** config.lua/config-local.lua for DB; `make -j$(nproc)` in MMOCoreORB.
- **TRE (Phase 7):** WSL = copy/symlink to `/trefiles`. Shadow = optional asset edit only.

## COMMIT & PUSH WORKFLOW (ORDER MATTERS)

**Reminder:** Commit and push to the **correct branch** in the **correct order**. Dev env goes last.

| What changed | Branch to use | When to commit/push |
|--------------|---------------|----------------------|
| **Game code** (Lua, C++, scripts, MMOCoreORB, content) | `Main` or your feature branch (e.g. `Ender_FeatureName`) | **First.** Commit and push code before touching dev env. |
| **Dev env files** (Cursor rules, skills, `.cursor/` context, workspace READMEs, WORKSPACE_STRUCTURE.md) | **Ender_CursorConfig** only | **Last.** After code is committed and pushed. |

**Work order:** (1) Make and test code on Shadow PC or WSL. (2) Commit and push **code** to the code branch. (3) If you updated rules/context/READMEs for both Shadow and WSL test dev, switch to **Ender_CursorConfig**, add those files, commit and push **last**. Nothing is ready for prod patch until code is tested on WSL dev server; dev env updates support both Shadow dev box and the WSL build/cmake/test server.

**Before you commit:** Confirm which branch you're on and whether you're committing code (code branch) or dev env (Ender_CursorConfig). Don't mix them.

## GIT / COLLAB (BOTH MACHINES)

1. Branch: `[DeveloperName]_[FeatureName]` (e.g. `Ender_MissingResources`). Never generic names.
2. No PRs. Push branch and notify Miphstoe or Hellguard in Discord for manual review.
3. Test locally on **WSL dev server** before committing (e.g. new mobs: spawn, kill, harvest, verify resource).

## DEV STACK

- C++, Lua. Shadow PC: Windows, Cursor, Git; no build/run. WSL dev server: WSL Debian, build/test/run; deps include build-essential, libmariadb-dev, liblua5.3-dev, cmake, etc.

